A 60:40 split leads to one of two things happening for UNOs. 1. You put your licences on the marketplace and get a decent return (a win). 2. You market your licences independently and can out compete the market (a win). The argument against this is that it can lead to slow adoption. Until rewards are good, there will always be slow adoption and any adoption will be driven by Uno marketing. Help UNOs with their marketing. Vote 60:40

